t as the world\u2019s most advanced hacker, working 24/7, except Anthropic wants it on defense, not offense.\n\nThe partners include Amazon, Apple, Google, Microsoft, NVIDIA, Broadcom, Cisco, JPMorgan, and the Linux Foundation.\n\n$CRWD and $PANW are the only two pure play cybersecurity companies Anthropic chose for this.\n\nFor that reason I\u2019m buying every single $CRWD dip.\n\nIf Anthropic is telling the world this model is too dangerous for a public release and they hand pick CrowdStrike to help defend against it, that tells you everything you need to know about where this company sits in the ecosystem.\n\nNot financial advice. Do your own research. I\u2019m just giving you guys insight into my thought process.", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 39, "replyCount": 52, "likeCount": 548, "quoteCount": 3, "viewCount": 258790, "createdAt": "Fri Apr 10 15:18:04 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 268, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2042623151201210837", "displayTextRange": [0, 277], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "pepemoonboy", "url": "https://x.com/pepemoonboy", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/pepemoonboy", "id": "1875040188159967232", "name": "Pepe Invests", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1877203408664305664/gCtVDjNI_normal.jpg", "coverPicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/1875040188159967232/1775319048", "description": "", "location": "Los Angeles, CA", "followers": 57327, "following": 320, "status": "", "canDm": true, "canMediaTag": true, "createdAt": "Fri Jan 03 04:43:26 +0000 2025", "entities": {"description": {"urls": []}, "url": {}}, "fastFollowersCount": 0, "favouritesCount": 34989, "hasCustomTimelines": true, "isTranslator": false, "mediaCount": 2077, "statusesCount": 39204, "withheldInCountries": [], "affiliatesHighlightedLabel": {}, "possibl